# HEADROOM INTEGRATION (OPTIONAL)

> Third-party: [Headroom](https://github.com/headroomlabs-ai/headroom) — Apache License 2.0  
> Docs: `integrations/headroom/README.md` or `agent-integrations/headroom/README.md`

## What it does

Compresses tool outputs, logs, files, and RAG chunks **before** they reach the LLM. Complements harness **token economy** (load fewer rules) with **context compression** (smaller payloads).

## One-time setup (human)

```bash
pip install "headroom-ai[all]"          # Python 3.10+
./agent-integrations/headroom/setup.sh --wrap
# Or: headroom wrap cursor — paste config in Cursor settings once
```

Proxy alternative: `headroom proxy --port 8787`

## Agent MUST NOT

- Assume Headroom is installed — it is optional per machine.
- Disable Headroom or change proxy settings without user request.
- Send secrets to Headroom cloud — it runs **locally**.

## With harness workflow

1. `resolve-rules.sh` — load 2–6 rule files
2. `generate-task-rules.sh` — optional task `.mdc`
3. Headroom — compresses context at LLM boundary (if user configured wrap/proxy)

